{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3487", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3487/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3487/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3487/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/datalad/datalad/issues/3487", "id": 459766908, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NTk3NjY5MDg=", "number": 3487, "title": "Q: Trajectory to make SSHConnection more useful", "user": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 63778594, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2Mzc3ODU5NA==", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/labels/question", "name": "question", "color": "fbca04", "default": true, "description": "Issue asks a question rather than reporting a problem"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2019-06-24T08:47:35Z", "updated_at": "2019-10-05T09:12:16Z", "closed_at": "2019-10-05T09:12:16Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I am using this functionality more and more, but it is rather clunky. For example, it is not easy to stream large outputs (think decompressing a remote archive and storing the output locally without making tmp copies, etc.\r\n\r\nI see two paths forward:\r\n\r\n1. Expose internal pieces, such as SSH command generation, so that could be used with an outside \"runner\".\r\n2. Add a dedicated `.run()` that sits on top of `subprocess.run()` and takes the same args.\r\n\r\n   https://docs.python.org/3/library/subprocess.html#subprocess.run\r\n\r\nThe later is PY3.5+ only, so we likely don't want to base internal functionality on it, but it would be very helpful in order to have the entire range of possibilities available via a standard interface, plus the connection handling functionality that we provide.\r\n\r\nIt also offers a cross-platform DEVNULL object (in addition to PIPE), which is really handy (PY 3.3+).\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3487/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laug